  • Preheat frying pan to medium.
  • Carefully shape your ground beef into 1 patty (use a little pressure as possible, this is the difference between a good burger to an awesome burger)
  • Salt, pepper, and garlic powder your paddy (don't be light on the seasoning)
  • Place seasoned beef patty into frying pan 3 minutes on each side
  • While beef is cooking toast up your pretzel bun in the toaster.
  • After toasting apply butter, garlic powder and 1k island dressing to your pretzel bun.
  • After beef is cooked, place the egg in the frying pan (I like it sunny side up and very runny)
  • Now combine and enjoy!!! Have napkins ready, its going to get messy!
